				<div class="headline_area">
					<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.xperiablog.net/2018/03/15/xperia-xz2-and-xa2-series-feature-seamless-updates/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent link to Xperia XZ2 and XA2 series feature Seamless Updates">Xperia XZ2 and XA2 series feature Seamless Updates</a></h2>
					<p class="headline_meta">by <span class="author vcard"><a href="http://www.xperiablog.net/author/xb/" class="url fn">XB</a></span> on <abbr class="published updated" title="2018-03-15">15th March 2018</abbr></p>
					<p class="headline_meta">in <span><a href="http://www.xperiablog.net/category/firmware/" rel="category tag">Firmware</a>, <a href="http://www.xperiablog.net/category/xperia-xa-series/" rel="category tag">Xperia XA series</a>, <a href="http://www.xperiablog.net/category/xperia-xz-series/" rel="category tag">Xperia XZ series</a></span></p>
				</div>
				<div class="format_text entry-content">
<p><img src="http://www.xperiablog.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Xperia-XA2-139x150.png" alt="" width="139" height="150" class="alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-47313" srcset="http://www.xperiablog.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Xperia-XA2-139x150.png 139w, http://www.xperiablog.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Xperia-XA2-315x339.png 315w, http://www.xperiablog.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Xperia-XA2.png 458w" sizes="(max-width: 139px) 100vw, 139px" />Sony Mobile has introduced support for <a href="https://source.android.com/devices/tech/ota/ab/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">A/B (Seamless) System Updates</a> in the Xperia XZ2 and XA2 series of phones. For those unaware, seamless updates were first introduced by Google in Android Nougat, but has not seen wide support from manufacturers until recently. It’s primarily the Google Pixel phones that have supported seamless updates up until now. </p>
<p>A phone that features seamless updates has two system partitions, A and B. When a firmware update arrives, it is downloaded and installed on the inactive partition. Once the update is installed on the inactive partition, the phone will reboot and switch to the partition with the newly updated firmware.  <a href="http://www.xperiablog.net/2018/03/15/xperia-xz2-and-xa2-series-feature-seamless-updates/#more-47309" class="more-link">[read more&hellip;]</a></p>
<p class="to_comments"><span class="bracket">{</span> <a href="http://www.xperiablog.net/2018/03/15/xperia-xz2-and-xa2-series-feature-seamless-updates/#comments" rel="nofollow"><span>53</span> comments</a> <span class="bracket">}</span></p>
				</div>
			</div>

