				<div class="headline_area">
					<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.xperiablog.net/2018/03/13/sony-explains-why-it-dropped-the-headphone-jack-for-the-xperia-xz2/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent link to Sony explains why it dropped the headphone jack for the Xperia XZ2">Sony explains why it dropped the headphone jack for the Xperia XZ2</a></h2>
					<p class="headline_meta">by <span class="author vcard"><a href="http://www.xperiablog.net/author/xb/" class="url fn">XB</a></span> on <abbr class="published updated" title="2018-03-13">13th March 2018</abbr></p>
					<p class="headline_meta">in <span><a href="http://www.xperiablog.net/category/xperia-xz-series/" rel="category tag">Xperia XZ series</a></span></p>
				</div>
				<div class="format_text entry-content">
<p><img src="http://www.xperiablog.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Xperia-XZ2-headphone-jack-195x150.png" alt="" width="195" height="150" class="alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-47291" srcset="http://www.xperiablog.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Xperia-XZ2-headphone-jack-195x150.png 195w, http://www.xperiablog.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Xperia-XZ2-headphone-jack-315x242.png 315w, http://www.xperiablog.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Xperia-XZ2-headphone-jack-640x493.png 640w, http://www.xperiablog.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Xperia-XZ2-headphone-jack.png 725w" sizes="(max-width: 195px) 100vw, 195px" />For all of Sony’s audio prowess, it still remains inexplicable to us that it decided to remove the 3.5mm headphone jack for the Xperia XZ2 and XZ2 Compact. A recent FAQ <a href="https://blogs.sonymobile.com/2018/03/04/sony-mobile-mwc-2018-faq/amp/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">published</a> by Sony explains that the headphone jack was dropped in order to accommodate the new ‘Ambient Flow’ design, as well as the “major market trend toward wireless headphones”. </p>
<p>This all seems like a bit of an excuse. We’re sure Sony could have made the room to include the jack if it really wanted to. After all, there are other manufacturers that have even slimmer bezels and still include the 3.5mm port.  <a href="http://www.xperiablog.net/2018/03/13/sony-explains-why-it-dropped-the-headphone-jack-for-the-xperia-xz2/#more-47289" class="more-link">[read more&hellip;]</a></p>
